-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BASF, EuroBank, Lloyds Banking 
-- 
-- Mon Oct 27, 2014 02:02AM EDT
-- None



Oct 27 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including BASF, Lloyds Banking and Shire, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * BASF <BASFn.DE>: JP Morgan cuts price target to 61 euros from 67 euros; rating underweight * EuroBank <EURBr.AT>: Citigroup raises to buy from neutral; target to 0.38 euros from 0.31 * Lloyds Banking <LLOY.L>: Jefferies cuts to underperform from hold * Shire <SHP.L>: Citigroup, Jefferies revise price target on the stockFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * BASF <BASFn.DE>: JP Morgan cuts price target to 61 euros from 67 euros; rating underweight * Buzzi Unicem <BZU.MI>: Jefferies raises target to 17.50 euros from 17.40 euros; rating buy * EuroBank <EURBr.AT>: Citigroup raises to buy from neutral; target to 0.38 euros from 0.31 * Lloyds Banking <LLOY.L>: Jefferies cuts to underperform from hold * SGS <SGSN.VX>: Jefferies cuts price target to Sfr 2300 from Sfr 2350; rating buy * Shire <SHP.L>: Jefferies cuts price target to 4,700p from 5,200p; rating buy * Shire <SHP.L>: Citigroup raises price target to 4900p from 4700p; rating buy * Spectris <SXS.L>: Morgan Stanley cuts price target to 2140p from 2300p; rating overweight * Vesuvius <VSVS.L>: Morgan Stanley cuts price target to 410p from 426p; rating underweight